{"id": "EUVD-2025-13231", "enisaUuid": "92a9d838-2163-3809-ab02-2ee27584c044", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: intel-ish-hid: ipc: Fix potential use-after-free in work function\n\nWhen a reset notify IPC message is received, the ISR schedules a work\nfunction and passes the ISHTP device to it via a global pointer\nishtp_dev. If ish_probe() fails, the devm-managed device resources\nincluding ishtp_dev are freed, but the work is not cancelled, causing a\nuse-after-free when the work function tries to access ishtp_dev. Use\ndevm_work_autocancel() instead, so that the work is automatically\ncancelled if probe fails.", "datePublished": "2025-05-02T18:31:32", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-12T21:30:59", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53039", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0a594cb490ca6232671fc09e2dc1a0fc7ccbb0b5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8ae2f2b0a28416ed2f6d8478ac8b9f7862f36785", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8c1d378b8c224fd50247625255f09fc01dcc5836", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d3ce3afd9f791dd1b7daedfcf8c396b60af5dec0"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53039", "GHSA-2352-43vg-7vcc"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0081145d-9c89-3866-94ae-d8a9c2f2ca2d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "0a74e002-4432-3351-9161-b861027a369c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <0a594cb490ca6232671fc09e2dc1a0fc7ccbb0b5"}, {"id": "1e2da51d-d05b-37e1-9214-d1a54424a70a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4.9"}, {"id": "5e576d1e-b4e2-3dc5-b961-e403b38963ac", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3"}, {"id": "6b179195-b404-35fa-bb18-1277bafbbb55", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ae02e5d40d5f829c589412c6253f925e35cf7a22 <8ae2f2b0a28416ed2f6d8478ac8b9f7862f36785"}, {"id": "6c82f807-5964-3a90-87ba-f50ed7db90bd", "produ